    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-11-16T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-11-16T05:00:00-05:00" n="376"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d376">
                <head>376. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in the Soviet Union</gloss>
                    to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d376fn0">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, PS 7-1 US-<gloss target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss> Barghoorn.
                        Confidential; Flash. Repeated to London.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Moscow</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1963-11-16T13:00:00+03:00">November 16, 1963, 1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1679. <persName corresp="#p_GAA1">Gromyko</persName> summoned me to <gloss
                        target="#t_MFA1">MFA</gloss> 12 noon today to inform me of <gloss
                        target="#t_SOV1">Sov</gloss> Govt decision, on personal intercession
                        <persName corresp="#p_KNS1">Khrushchev</persName>, to expel <persName
                        corresp="#p_BFC1">Barghoorn</persName> from <gloss target="#t_USSR1"
                        >USSR</gloss>, probably today. Action by Sov Govt, <persName
                        corresp="#p_GAA1">Gromyko</persName> said reading from prepared statement,
                    was in response deep concern expressed by President. He stressed <persName
                        corresp="#p_BFC1">Barghoorn</persName> clearly guilty of espionage as
                    evidenced by documents found on his person and by his own deposition.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_GAA1">Gromyko</persName> voiced expectation on
                        behalf<gloss target="#t_SOV1">Sov</gloss> Govt that US Govt would take steps
                    immediately release Ivanov. Finally, he pointed out if any US official should
                    attempt publicly justify <persName corresp="#p_BFC1">Barghoorn</persName>ʼs
                    conduct and thus cast doubt on Sov action against him <gloss target="#t_SOV1"
                        >Sov</gloss>s would publish results investigation.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_GAA1">Gromyko</persName> said <gloss target="#t_MFA1"
                        >MFA</gloss> would be in touch later today with Consular Section re details
                    release <persName corresp="#p_BFC1">Barghoorn</persName>. In response my
                    inquiry, he confirmed <gloss target="#t_SOV1">Sov</gloss>s would make brief
                    announcement of release to press this evening and indicated no objection our
                    doing likewise. Accordingly, <gloss target="#t_EMB1">Emb</gloss> plans inform
                    local American correspondents later today, preferably after firm word on release
                    time received. <gloss target="#t_EMB1">Emb</gloss> intends limit remarks to
                    press to brief statement <gloss target="#t_SOV1">Sov</gloss> Govt had decided
                    release <persName corresp="#p_BFC1">Barghoorn</persName> in recognition
                    Presidentʼs expressed concern at his arrest and will decline further
                    comment.</p>
                <p>Full text <persName corresp="#p_GAA1">Gromyko</persName>ʼs statement follows
                        immediately.<note n="1" xml:id="d376fn1">Transmitted in telegram 1680,
                        November 16. (Ibid.)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Stoessel</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
